<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-638-613  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 638 613.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Oct 15 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Japan: DTP system from Justsystem. (desktop publishing equipment)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Yazawa, Naoyuki.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   JustSystem (Products).andO;Topic:     New ProductDesktop publishingSoftware packagesSubsidiary CompaniesSupport ServicesPeripherals.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>JAPAN: DTP SYSTEM FROM JUSTSYSTEM TOKUSHIMA, JAPAN, 1990 OCT 15 (NB) --Justsystem, which made a killing with its Japanese word processing softwareIchitaro, has announced the start of a desktop publishing hardware businessand has established a 100 percent owned subsidiary for its maintenance.andM;The system, dubbed Super DTP &quot;Daichi&quot; System 70, costs 5,800,000 yen or$44,615 in a basic configuration -- laser printer, DTP controller box andhigh resolution display.andP;  The Editing System excluding laser printer costs3,940,000 yen or $30,310.andM;The system requires a 32-bit PC-9800 series of NEC as host and DTP softwarecalled Daichi Ver.andP;  1.01.andP;  The DTP software has integrated instructions withJustsystem's leading programs, such as Ichitaro word processing software andHanako graphic software and its data is compatible with either.andM;The software house has procured the necessary hardware, including the displayand printer, from an undisclosed electronics maker on an OEM (originalequipment manufacturing) basis.andP;  The systems will be sold under the Justbrand name.andM;Meanwhile, the firm has founded a subsidiary called Justsystem Engineeringfor support and maintenance of the systems that are sold.andP;  It expects 2,400systems to be sold in the initial year.andM;(Naoyuki Yazawa/19901011/Press Contact: Justsystem Corp., 0886-55-1121)</TEXT></DOC>